  description: 'In 1962, the Joint Chiefs of Staff signed a top-secret plan to stage terrorist attacks on American soil — bombings, hijackings, even sinking a boatload of refugees — to justify an invasion of Cuba. President Kennedy killed the plan and fired the general who proposed it. Thirty-five years later, the documents were finally declassified.',
